{{Infobox person |name = Karl-Heinz Werner Toosbuy |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_name = Hanni Toosbuy |birth_date = {{birth date|1928|02|23|df=y}} |birth_place = Holte, Denmark |death_date = {{Death date and age|2004|06|08|1928|02|23|df=y}} |death_place = |residence = |nationality = Danish |ethnicity = |citizenship = |other_names = |known_for = Owner and founder of [[ECCO]] |education = |alma_mater = |occupation = |years_active = |home_town = |salary = |networth = |title = |term = |predecessor = |successor = |boards = |religion = |spouse = Birte Toosbuy |partner = |children = [[Hanni Toosbuy Kasprzak]] |parents = |relations = |website = }}
'''Karl-Heinz Werner Toosbuy''' (23 February 1928 – 8 June 2004) was a Danish businessman, the founder and owner of [[ECCO]], the Danish shoe company.
Karl Toosbuy trained as a shoemaker and by his early 30s, was running a [[Copenhagen]] factory. In 1963, he moved with his wife Birte and daughter Hanni to [[Bredebro]] on the west coast of Denmark, just north of the German border. Toosbuy started ECCO in what had been an empty factory.<ref name="ecco">{{cite web|url=http://global.ecco.com/en/company/heritage|publisher=global.ecco.com|title=ECCO.com|accessdate=2016-09-10}}</ref>
He died on 8 June 2004.<ref name="leathermag">{{cite web|url=http://www.leathermag.com/features/featurekarl-toosbuy-dies/|publisher=leathermag.com|title=Karl Toosbuy dies - Leather International|accessdate=2016-09-10}}</ref>
