'''Sevan Bıçakçı''' (born 1965 in [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]) is a famed [[Turkish people|Turkish]] jeweller of [[Armenians|Armenian]] descent. He is one of the few renowned jewelers in Turkey and is known around the world.<ref name=jabeel>{{cite news|title=Muslim art in hand of an Armenian|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/english/lifestyle/12040055.asp?scr=1|accessdate=13 March 2013|newspaper=Hurriyet}}</ref> He is considered a "star jeweler" in Turkey.<ref>{{cite news|title=Middle Eastern jewellery designers take centre stage at Christie's|url=http://www.ameinfo.com/228099.html|accessdate=13 March 2013|newspaper=Ameinfo}}</ref>
== Life and career == Of [[Armenians|Armenian]] descent,<ref name="Sevan Bicakci">{{cite news|last=M. Forte|first=Pauline|title=Turkish delights: The Ringmaster.|url=http://gulfnews.com/life-style/beauty-fashion/turkish-delights-the-ringmaster-1.474647|accessdate=26 November 2012|newspaper=The Gulf News|date=February 12, 2009}}</ref>Sevan Bıçakçı was born in 1965 in the [[Fatih]] district of [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]. He is known as the 'King of Rings'. At the age of 12, his father, who was a theater actor,{{citation needed|date=December 2012}} placed Sevan under the apprenticeship of Hovsep Catak in the [[Grand Bazaar, Istanbul|Grand Bazaar]] of Istanbul. After serving 4 years of apprenticeship, his master died. However, he had learned a great deal about jewellery design and craftsmanship. He then opened a workshop in order to serve bigger manufacturers as a freelance jewel designer.<ref name="Sevan Bicakci"/> He worked on his first collection for a year before unveiling it in the global market in 2002.<ref name="Sevan Bicakci"/> His jewelry designs are that of Byzantine and Ottoman styles. Some of Sevan Bıçakçı's famous clientele include [[Catherine Zeta-Jones]], [[Elizabeth Hurley]], [[Celine Dion]], [[Liv Tyler]], [[Mariah Carey]], [[Brooke Shields]], [[Angie Harmon]], [[Kim Raver]], [[Halle Berry]], [[Mary Kate Olsen|Mary Kate]] and [[Ashley Olsen]], [[Michelle Monaghan]], and [[Tory Burch]].<ref name="Lord of the Rings">{{cite web|title=SEVAN BICAKCI: "Lord of the Rings"|url=http://www.osterjewelers.com/jewelry/designers/SevanBicakci|publisher=Oster Jewellers|accessdate=26 November 2012}}</ref>
== Awards == Sevan Bıçakçı has received many distinguished awards such as:<ref name="womenist.net">{{cite web|title=Sevan Bicakci|url=http://www.womenist.net/en/p-145/jewellery/sevan_bicakci.html|publisher=Womenist|accessdate=26 November 2012}}</ref> * Town and Country Couture Award. (Three times in a row). * Turkish Gold Design Award * He was nominated for the Jameel Prize Award<ref name=jabeel /> * He was also nominated as the top five most noteworthy free lance jewelry designers by the Tanzanite Foundation.
