{{Infobox person | name = | image = Sherin Naiken.jpeg | image_size = 230px | alt = | caption = Sherin Naiken at the launch of the ''Sesel sa!'' video competition in 2016 | birth_name = Sherin Naiken | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|03|30}} | birth_place = [[Anse Royale]], [[Mahé, Seychelles|Mahé]], Seychelles | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (date of death first) --> | death_place = | nationality = Seychellois | other_names = | occupation = {{flatlist| *[[economist]] *[[Financial management|finance expert]]}} | alma_mater = {{flatlist| *[[University of Manchester]] *[[University of London]]}} | years_active = 2006{{ndash}}present | spouse = Marco Francis | employer = [[Seychelles Tourism Board]] | children = {{Collapsible list|titlestyle=font-weight:normal; background:transparent; text-align:left; |title = 2 |1=Elisabeth|2=Emma}} | parents = | known_for = | notable_works = }}
'''Sherin Naiken''' (born March 30, 1984) is a Seychellois [[economist]] and [[Financial management|finance expert]]. She is the [[chief executive officer]] of the [[Seychelles Tourism Board]], since July 1, 2013. Under her leadership, tourism has increased with specific campaigns targeting markets such as the United Kingdom.
==Early life and education== Naiken was born and grew up in the [[Anse Royale]] administrative district of [[Mahé, Seychelles|Mahé]], Seychelles, where she completed her early education.<ref name="sn"/> She holds a B.Sc degree in Economics and Business Studies from the [[University of Manchester]], [[United Kingdom|U.K]]; and an M.Sc degree in [[Finance]] from the [[University of London]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pfsr.org/news/sherin-naiken-the-ceo-of-the-seychelles-tourism-board-and-mother-of-two-qualifies-with-a-master-of-science-in-finance/|title=Sherin Naiken, the CEO of the Seychelles Tourism Board and mother of two qualifies with a Master of Science in Finance|work=Seychelles Ministry of Tourism and Culture|date=|accessdate=9 August 2016}}</ref>
==Career== She started her career in 2006 at the Ministry of National Development as an industrial officer before she rose through the ranks to become director of investment promotion.<ref name="sn">{{cite news|url=http://www.nation.sc/article.html?id=250550|title=Up Close … with Sherin Naiken|work=[[Seychelles Nation]]|date=9 August 2016|accessdate=9 August 2016}}</ref> In July 2013, she was appointed CEO of the [[Seychelles Tourism Board]], succeeding Elsia Grandcourt.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.seychelles.travel/en/newsletter/609-e-newsletter-issue-76-76/seychelles-tourism-board-76-183/4050-sherin-naiken-appointed-new-chief-executive-of-seychelles-tourism-board-sherin-naiken-appointed-new-chief-executive-of-seychelles-tourism-board|title=Sherin Naiken Appointed New Chief Executive Of Seychelles Tourist Board|work=Seychelles Travel|date=|accessdate=9 August 2016}}</ref>
In 2015, she remained upbeat about the tourism prospect of the islands, attributing the economic reforms of the government for the increase of visitors early in the year, particularly from the UK and France. She also linked this with a marketing drive executed under her leadership of the tourism board, with the campaign "luxury within reach" targeting potential visitors in the UK. To further promote this work, she appeared in interviews with the [[BBC]], ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' and [[CNN]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Meriton-Jean|first1=Sharon|title=Seychelles Tourism Board CEO live on CNN: Hint of recovery in European tourism arrivals to the islands|url=http://www.seychellesnewsagency.com/articles/2525/Seychelles+Tourism+Board+CEO+live+on+CNN+Hint+of+recovery+in+European+tourism+arrivals+to+the+islands|accessdate=6 November 2016|work=Seychelles News Agency|date=9 March 2015}}</ref>
==Personal life== She is married to Marco Francis, a businessman and former chairman of the [[Seychelles Chamber of Commerce and Industry]]. Together, they have two children.<ref name="sn"/>
