{{Peacock|date=October 2009}} [[Image:WilliamHeinecke.jpg|thumb|William Heinecke, 2006]]
'''William Ellwood Heinecke''' ({{lang-th|วิลเลียม เอ็ลล์วู๊ด ไฮเน็ค}}; born 1949) is an American-born [[Thailand|Thai]] businessman. He is the CEO and Chairman of [[Minor Corporation]], the CEO and Chairman of [[Minor International]], and Chairman of [[Minor Food Group]].<ref name="Forbes">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/global/2009/1005/thailand-richest-09-william-heinecke-excellent-adventure.html|first=Ron|last=Gluckman|title=Bill's Excellent Adventure|work=Forbes Asia Magazine|date=2009-10-05|accessdate=2013-03-02}}</ref>
==Biography== Heinecke moved to Bangkok in 1963 at age 14 with his family, having previously lived in Japan, Hong Kong and Malaysia. Heinecke's father spent 25 years in the United States military, serving in [[World War II]] and the [[Korean War]]. When he retired, he joined the foreign service. His mother was an Asia correspondent for ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine. Heinecke studied at the [[International School Bangkok]],<ref name="Forbes"/> and persuaded the editor of the now defunct [[Bangkok World]] to let him write a weekly column on [[go-carting]]. In return, he received advertising space alongside it.<ref name="EscapeArtist">{{cite news|url=http://www.escapeartist.com/efam18/Expats_In_Asia.html|first=Harold|last=Stephens|title=Expats In Asia: Bill Heinecke, Entrepreneur Extraordianaire|work=Escape Artist}}</ref>
At age 17, while still a high school student, Heinecke took over from the Bangkok World's advertising manager.<ref name="EscapeArtist"/> One year later, he founded Inter-Asian Enterprise, to supply office cleaning services, and Inter-Asian Publicity, a radio advertising company, using US$1,200 he had borrowed{{Citation needed|date=August 2010}}. He later sold Inter-Asia Publicity to [[Ogilvy & Mather]]. In 1967, he founded Minor Holdings, which would over the next four decades would grow into The Minor Group, including more than 30 companies.{{Citation needed|date=August 2010}}.<ref name="Forbes"/><ref name="Wharton">{{cite news|url=http://www.whartonhcmc08.com/bio-heinecke.html|title=Speaker Biography: William Heinecke|publisher=Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania|date=2008-05-30|accessdate=2013-03-02}}</ref>
Heinecke had his first hotel venture in 1978, the Royal Garden Resort in [[Pattaya]]. His business ventures have included advertising agencies and other hotels in [[Bangkok]], [[Hua Hin]], [[Phuket (city)|Phuket]], [[Chiang Mai]], [[Chiang Rai]] as well as outside of Thailand. He also introduced American-style fast foods to Thailand in the late 1970s and 1980s – brands like [[Mister Donut]], [[The Pizza Company]] and [[Burger King]].{{Citation needed|date=August 2010}} Heinecke naturalized as a [[Thai nationality law|Thai citizen]] in 1991, [[renunciation of United States citizenship|renouncing United States citizenship]] in the process.<ref name="Forbes"/><ref name="Wharton"/> He was the president of the American Chamber of Commerce in Thailand and sat on the Prime Minister’s Foreign Investment Advisory Council. He is a supporter of the Thai Elephant Conservation Centre, and authored ''The Entrepreneur'', which has been translated into a number of languages.{{Citation needed|date=August 2010}}
==Minor International== {{Main|Minor International}}
Minor International Plc is one of the largest hospitality and leisure companies in the Asia Pacific region. The company's hotels and resorts are operated under the Four Seasons, Marriott Resort & Spa, Anantara and other brands in Thailand, Vietnam, the Maldives, the Middle East and Indonesia, and its spa brands like Mandara and Anantara have consistently been named among the best in the world. Minor Corporation manufactures and markets fashion, cosmetics and leisure brands, while Minor International currently operates 16 hotels and resorts and more than 630 branded food service outlets across Asia and the Middle East.<ref name="Forbes"/>
===Awards=== In 2013, Heinecke received the ABLF Trailblazer Award from the Asian Business Leadership Forum (ABLF) Awards held in Dubai, UAE managed by [[Indian Expressions]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zawya.com/story/The_Asian_Business_Leadership_Forum_ABLF_Awards-ZAWYA20131215134016/|title=The Asian Business Leadership Forum (ABLF) Awards|author=|date=|website=Zawya.com|accessdate=1 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/kt-article-display-1.asp?xfile=/data/uaebusiness/2013/December/uaebusiness_December180.xml&section=uaebusiness|title=Statesmen, business leaders honoured at ABLF Awards|date=|website=Khaleejtimes.com|accessdate=1 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ablfawards.com/winners/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-02-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701231021/http://www.ablfawards.com/winners/ |archive-date=2013-07-01 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
